ain backgrounds displayed COC values that were higher in <italic>pch2&#x00394;</italic> than in wild-type (<xref ref-type="table" rid="pgen-1000571-t005">Table 5</xref>). For three intervals, interference could not be detected in either wild-type or <italic>pch2&#x00394;</italic>. In one interval, interference was seen in wild-type, but not <italic>pch2&#x00394;</italic>. For the remaining four intervals, interference was seen in both wild-type and <italic>pch2&#x00394;</italic>, but was weaker in <italic>pch2&#x00394;</italic>.</p><table-wrap id="pgen-1000571-t005" position="float"><object-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1371/journal.pgen.1000571.t005</object-id><label>Table 5</label><caption><title>Interference calculations using coefficients of coincidence.</title></caption><alternatives><graphic id="pgen-1000571-t005-5" xlink:href="pgen.1000571.t005"/><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><colgroup span="1"><col align="left" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/></colgroup><thead><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">4-spore viable tetrads</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">DCO obs.</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">DCO exp.</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">COC</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">p</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">I</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan="7" align="left" rowspan="1"><bold>Chromosome XV</bold></td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><bold><italic>URA3-LEU2-LYS2</italic></bold></td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan=